        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-12-19T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-12-19T10:00:00-05:00" n="374"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                <head>374. Memorandum of a Conversation, Turkish <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss> Delegation Headquarters, Paris, December 19, 1957, 4 p.m.<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d374fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 411.8241/2–3157. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_RSW1"
                            >Rockwell</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>/MC/37</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1957-12-19T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1957, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States</hi>
                        <list>
                            <item>The President</item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_RSW1">Rockwell</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Turkey</hi>
                        <list>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MA1">Adnan Menderes</persName>, Prime
                                Minister of Turkey</item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ZFR1">Fatin Zorlu</persName>, Foreign
                                Minister of Turkey</item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EM1">Melih Esenbel</persName>, Secretary
                                General of the Turkish Foreign Office</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Economic Assistance to Turkey</item>
                </list>
                <p>Speaking on behalf of the Prime Minister, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ZFR1"
                        >Zorlu</persName> said that Turkey needed US support to help it overcome its
                    economic difficulties. Turkey was grateful for what the US had already done. She
                    was now taking measures to improve her budgetary situation and control
                    inflation, and hoped the US would help her in this task. The US should speed up
                    the current aid which has not yet been received, and give increased aid in
                    addition.</p>
                <p>The Prime Minister said that, with US help, in around three years Turkey would be
                    in very good shape. Russian pressure made it more urgent than ever that Turkish
                    economic measures be successful. The three-year drought had been a severe blow.
                    The problem of the increase in population was also involved, added Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZFR1">Zorlu</persName>.</p>
                <p>The Secretary said that he was aware of the statement Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MA1">Menderes</persName> had made to Ambassador
                        <persName>Warren</persName> about the measures the government would take to
                    stabilize the economy.<note n="2" xml:id="d374fn2">In telegram 1648, December
                        12, <persName>Warren</persName> informed the Department that in discussions
                        with <persName corresp="#p_MA1">Menderes</persName> on December 10, the
                        Prime Minister had requested the Ambassador to inform his government that
                        Turkey was taking steps to “lower price structure” and to “stabilize Turkish
                        money”. <persName corresp="#p_MA1">Menderes</persName> also noted that the
                        recent elections had revealed an increase in “Communist pressures” on
                        Turkey. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi> 782.5–<gloss target="#t_MSP1"
                            >MSP</gloss>/12–1257)</note> He would look into this matter in response
                    to the Prime Minister’s request that he give it his personal attention.</p>
            </div>
